I do not believe you can actually “teach” someone to be a songwriter, however, there are ways to set yourself up for success.  I can only share my experience and the habits that have helped me to open the lines of creativity and to say/write something that matters…even if only to me. I write songs because I have to, and if you have that same desire, I think this class could give you some tools to get started and to follow through.  I feel like it could easily be called “songwriting for dummies” because I am no scholar or prolific musician, but I’m living proof that anyone can write a song if they have the passion and a story to tell…and we all have that. 

So that being said…calling all songwriters, producers, and artists — enrollment for my upcoming songwriting class on @studio is now open. Seats are limited for this 10-week class, so sign up now at studio.com/shane (link in bio).
The Baums and Fullers take Morocco.

We had the chance to spend some time with these Samburu children in Kenya.  They taught Dash and Dylan songs in Swahili.  They stumbled through trying to pronounce our names and laughed at our pronunciation of theirs.  When it was time for us to go, I asked if I could get a pic.  It was 2 hours later that I sent the picture to my sister and she messaged back “did you notice that Dash is holding hands with that little girl next to him?” I have no idea how I missed this and I’m still not over it.  This boy who runs 90 mph nonstop everyday driving us crazy about video games and basketball courts and constantly annoying his sister.  I have questioned whether or not they have gotten anything from this year of travel and if it will spoil them beyond repair…then this picture happened.  I keep zooming in and staring at her little hand in his.  I asked him about it later and he said “she held her hand out and I just took it” - if we could all just do that.  When someone reaches their hand out…just take it.  She wasn’t asking for anything but a friend. We have had the opportunity to see things that most people don’t even know to dream about.  I have gotten every angle of every perfectly lit window of every castle and temple and church across the world, but nothing means as much as this picture.

6am this morning watching the news…this is the first time that kids are crying over snow.  No birthday party today, but we’re letting them have their cakes for breakfast and that seems to be softening the blow. I think we’re taking it harder than them, so I will also be having cake for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. Happy double digits to our double D’s…your Dads are obsessed with you.

I spent our snow day looking at 10 years worth of pictures of all the friends and family who have helped us survive fatherhood, and who constantly remind us that we’re not even to the hard part. We definitely had no idea what we were in for with these 2 amazing maniacs, and really have no idea what’s in store…but, we know we wouldn’t trade one second.  Here’s to our first decade of being Dash and Dylan’s Dads…I put as many pics as I could into 90 seconds.  I also could only tag 20 people, which is about 1/5 of the village that we have counted on, leaned on, and been loved on by.

He will be so embarrassed for me posting this, but luckily I live for embarrassing my kids. My mom LOVED to convince us we weren’t getting what we wanted for our birthdays or Christmas.  She would go to great lengths and had these intricate stories about how they were out of stock, or she didn’t have the money (which she really didn’t), or it wasn’t gonna make it in time, or she had waited too long to buy it…sometimes she would even cry and apologize and have us crying and saying it was ok, before the perfect gift would magically appear…well, I am happy to report her legacy is well in tact and that we had Dash so convinced we couldn’t get this video game for his birthday, thus this amazing and sweet reaction.  THIS is the spirit of Christmas: scare your kids until they cry.
Joy from the World 🌎 🎄 ♥️

The week Dash and Dylan were born in Palm Springs, @rhorn1 & @thebrandyclark flew out to meet them and to discuss the first outline of the show that is now called “Shucked”. It was born in the same place at the same time as my kids and is definitely like my 3rd child.  These 2 have shared their Dad with this show for the whole first decade of their lives, and if their other Dad (better known as Pop) hadn’t stepped up and supported and believed, I never would have made it all the way to Broadway with this little show about corn.  Yesterday I got to show the kids the marquis and Pop came through again by grabbing my now favorite picture with my 3 children.
Happy Valentine’s Day from Dash & Rocky

Fishing for and swimming with piranhas, playing with sloths, pink dolphins, crocs, snakes, and centipedes…all things I never thought I would do, and probably don’t need to do again…but, I am so happy we made the trip to the Amazon because we met some of the most amazing people and learned and laughed more than should be allowed. Here’s a few of my favorite memories…

For everything we had heard about Ecuador, nothing could have prepared us for the mind blowing wildlife and breathtaking beauty of the Galápagos Islands.  If you ever have the chance…I cannot encourage you enough…GO!!! I am already dreaming of when we can go back.

The first gathering at the Covenant elementary school since the unthinkable 3 weeks ago…this is not a coincidence.  This is God. These are angels.  I am not a Bible thumper, nor do I judge anyone who is, but I am in awe of the message God wrote 3000 years ago that would be so obviously meant for this moment in this place for these families and friends  to heal and give hope for peace…this is the EXACT passage as it is written: “I have set my rainbow in the clouds and it will be the sign of the COVENANT between me and the earth. I will remember my COVENANT between me and you and all living creatures of every kind. Never again will the waters become a flood to destroy all life.  Whenever the rainbow appears in the clouds, I will see it and remember the everlasting COVENANT between God and all living creatures of every kind on the earth.” Genesis 9:13-16

@thebrandyclark @rhorn1 and I started working 10 years ago on this little country music musical, and yesterday it was nominated for 9 Tony awards. So many times I wanted to quit.  So many times I wondered if anyone would ever care enough to buy a ticket to see this show.  So many months that added up to years spent writing then re-writing then scrapping it all and starting from scratch…but, it’s all a beautiful blur because I was surrounded by people who believed when I couldn’t anymore…who dreamed when I was way too afraid to. If you swipe, you’ll see the names and faces of people who were recognized by the Tony’s yesterday…what you won’t see are all the shoulders we stood on to get this across the finish line.  People who took this show on as their own and created a community and a family and a town where I wish the whole world could live.  I am in awe of the talent and persistence and heart of these people and I am so grateful that they kept this going when so many times I was terrified we would never get here.  I’m so glad I stayed.  This has truly been the greatest journey of my life.  If there’s something you want to do, please don’t let the fear of failing keep you from doing it.

The Dad who takes 10 year old twins to Antarctica while the other Dad stays in NYC to make one of his wildest dreams come true.  The Dad who polar plunges with those kids while the other Dad is in a warm hotel room.  The Dad who packs the bags, arranges the travel, makes sure everyone has eaten, and makes everyone laugh 24/7. Happy Fathers Day, Pop. If it weren’t for you…we would all be stuck at a train station somewhere in BFE while the other Dad looks at his phone and complains about there being no Starbucks in BFE.
“Boy him and I are different” — @shanemcanally 😂😂😂😂 Episode 2 of Orange Country is out now. New episodes every Wednesday!

This guy spent his birthday going to MY high school reunion and re-listening to stories he’s heard, at least, 100 times…then today he braved my FAMILY reunion where 50 of my uncles/aunts/cousins told even more stories that he had heard and some he probably didn’t need to.  He never mentioned his birthday or complained that it was 112 degrees (this is the actual temperature). This IG post and this sign in my hometown is all he got for his 49th trip around the sun. I’ll just say…we sure do love you, Pop.  The world is a whole lot better for you being in it. Here’s to 49 more.

“My Chi-Chi’s name is Chelsea.” 4 years of missing our Chi-Chi.  4 years of rainbows and butterflies and constant reminders that as bad as we wish we had her here to hug and hold, she’s never far away.  My friend.  My sister.  Our partner in the first 7 years of our family.  We physically went from 5 to 4, but our angel army grew by infinity 4 years ago.  I wish it were different, but I wouldn’t trade the years we had for anything in the world.  Every single night we snuggle the kids under their Chi-Chi blankets and say the same words they said to her every night: “Hug…kiss…I love you.” Repeat. Repeat. Repeat.
When your best friend accidentally outs you to your kids 😅 hear more from @shanemcanally in episode 15, out now!
